46. (BOOK 5. 5.)

Pliny is sorry to lose his friend Fannius—sorry that he died before he could alter his will, but still more sorry that he has left unfrnished his history of Nero¹s victims, a circumstance which had been intimated to Fannius himself by a strange vision.
